# ORIG TITLE    Tomic senior in court not on court . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Thomas Drouet, the training partner of ATP player Bernard Tomic, has accused the players father of assault. John Tomic is due to face charges in Madrid on May 14. It is alleged the incident happened at an airport when Tomic senior spat in the Frenchman’s face and then head-butted him. Drouet said John Tomic, who acts as his son’s coach, had treated him like a dog. It is not the first time Tomic has been in the news. At the 2012 Miami Masters his son asked the umpire to eject his father from the crowd during one of his matches. 
